Mince the scallions keeping the white and green parts separate (the greens will be used for a garnish). In a soup pot, add the chicken stock, chicken, white portion of scallions, bamboo shoots, halved mushrooms, hot peppers, Splenda, soy sauce, vinegar and guar gum. Stir well. Bring to a slow boil for about 10 minutes. Reduce to a simmer. When ready to serve, remove from heat and very slowly swirl in the egg.